body: Although her name means "snow white," Shirayuki is a cheerful, red-haired girl living in the country of Tanbarun who works diligently as an apothecary at her herbal shop. Her life changes drastically when she is noticed by the silly prince of Tanbarun, Prince Raji, who then tries to force her to become his concubine. Unwilling to give up her freedom, Shirayuki cuts her long red hair and escapes into the forest, where she is rescued from Raji by Zen Wistalia, the second prince of a neighboring country, and his two aides. Hoping to repay her debt to the trio someday, Shirayuki sets her sights on pursuing a career as the court herbalist in Zen's country, Clarines.

body: [[laby (elsword)|Laby]]'s [[mirror]], which absorbs all of her sadness and grief. Nisha's appearance changes depending on which class tree Laby pursues. In Laby's third tree, it takes a darker appearance, seeming to break down while its liquid component spills out. Upon reaching [[nisha labyrinth (elsword)|Nisha Labyrinth]], she gains her own physical form that mostly resembles Laby aside from having dark blue as her main color scheme, and she takes over as the playable character while Laby becomes the energy in the mirror.

title: shouji
body:
[b]Shouji[/b] (障子) are a type of [[door]], [[window]], or room divider in traditional [[east asian architecture|Japanese architecture]]. They consist of thin, translucent paper on a wooden lattice frame. The paper is thin enough to let light in, but not to see through.

Shouji can be used as [[sliding doors]] or as windows. Sometimes, shouji panels may include a small glass window to see through.

Shouji are similar to [[fusuma]], another type of sliding paper panel. The difference is that [[fusuma]] are made of thick, opaque paper that doesn't let light through.

title: tv_camera
body:
A large professional high-end video camera used by television studios and other businesses or organizations that need such devices.  Three major types of these are: studio cameras, Electronic News Gathering (ENG) cameras (like those used with field reporters), and Electronic Field Production (EFP) cameras (likes those used to broadcast professional sports). 

Only ENG cameras have the ability to record, making them similar to consumer [[camcorder]]s, although they tend to be much larger, heavier, and have a variety of other differences.  Studio and EFP cameras lack the ability to record anything and are tethered by cables to the other equipment that records and/or transmits the video for broadcasting.

h4. See also

* [[video camera]]

title: movie_camera
body:
A camera that captures a rapid succession of pictures onto film.  By playing the film in an appropriate projector, the images can be viewed in rapid succession to produce an animated picture of what was originally viewed by the camera.  

Not to be confused with the [[camcorder]] tag, which is a portable device that is composed of a video camera and video recorder.  These devices use electronic motion picture acquisition, instead taking a rapid sequence of photos to film, and tend to look very different.

title: symmetra_(overwatch)
body:
[i]"The true enemy of humanity is disorder."[/i]

Real Name: Satya Vaswani
Age: 28
Occupation: Architech
Country: India

A support-class character in [[Overwatch]]. After she was identified as one of the few capable of becoming a light-bending architech, Satya was plucked from extreme poverty and placed in the care of Vishkar's Architech Academy, never to return home. Isolated and lonely in her new life, Satya immersed herself in her education and training. Satya approached hard-light manipulation differently than her peers by weaving her constructs in the motions of the traditional dance of her homeland. Her abilities earned her the moniker "Symmetra".

VA: Anjani Bhimani (English), [[nabatame_hitomi|Hitomi Nabatame]] (Japanese), Carla Castañeda (Latin American Spanish), Silvia Sarmentera (European Spanish), Tulika Srivastava (French)

title: sakata_kintoki_(gintama)
body:
[[Gintama]] character. He has straight and golden hair and also light blue eyes. He wears the opposite color of Gintoki by having white boots, white shirt and pants with blue linings, and a black yukata with golden patterns worn sloppily, draped over his left shoulder like Gintoki.

All is opposite from Gintoki. 

He was built by [[Hiraga Gengai]] by orders of [[Kagura (Gintama)|Kagura]] and [[Shimura Shinpachi]] who were mad at [[Sakata Gintoki|Gintoki]] for leaving them behind. In order for them to keep doing their work they decided to came up with ideas to make the perfect yorozuya substitute leader that would fill in Gintoki's spot when he was absent. 

His seiyuu is [[Nakamura Yuuichi]].

Not to be confused with [[Sakata Gintoki]]. While similarly named to [[Kintarou]], his character is not directly based on him.

title: rukino_saki
body:
One of the main characters of [i][[Kakumeiki Valvrave]][/i] and the main protagonist of the spin-off manga "Kakumeiki Valvrave: Ryuusei no Valkyrie":[http://myanimelist.net/manga/52239/Kakumeiki_Valvrave:_Ryuusei_no_Valkyrie].

A popular idol who has grown aloof due to her career being on hold. It is hinted that she has romantic feelings for [[Tokishima Haruto|Haruto]] but keeps them to herself knowing of his feelings for [[Sashinami Shouko|Shouko]] . She is one of the few people who knows about Haruto's power. She and Haruto discover the other Valvrave models hidden in Module 77. Saki enters the cockpit and becomes the pilot of [[Valvrave IV]] (coded VVVIV), to which she names "Carmilla", as well as being injected with the same substance as Haruto thus gaining the same powers as him (like transferring to another body).

Saki is a beautiful pale-skinned young girl with silky back-length [[black hair]] and [[purple eyes|violet eyes]]. She wears the traditional Sakimori Academy uniform which she pairs with black knee-high socks and light brown boots. In an angle, she wears a white [[hair ornament]].

title: valvrave_iv
body:
A [[mecha]] from [[Kakumeiki Valvrave]].

The [b]RM-047 Valvrave IV Hinowa[/b] is the second Valvrave to take an active role in the series and piloted by [[Rukino Saki]]. Its official name is Hinowa, but is later nicknamed Carmilla by Saki.

Valvrave IV is a high mobility weapon, designed to quickly take out any type of enemy from any range. Using its specially designed Multi-Leg Spine to quickly accelerate or change direction at high speed, it can outmaneuver machines with traditional thrusters, outrun missiles, and even outpace the other Valvraves. It is equipped with the Mirror Rave engine, a replica of [[Valvrave I]]'s Rave engine.

Valvrave IV's weaponry is considered unique, even amongst the other Valvraves; its Spindle Knuckles can be launched and controlled in mid-flight, allowing them to fly all over the battlefield, slicing through enemies at the pilot's discretion.

First appearing in [[Dragon Ball Online]] before being re-implemented in [[Dragon Ball Heroes]] and [[Dragon Ball Xenoverse]], the [b]Masked Saiyan[/b] is a brainwashed [[Bardock]], adorned with a white mask with the symbol of the Time Breakers (who consist of [[towa_(dragon_ball)|Towa]] and [[mira_(dragon_ball)|Mira]]) on its forehead, and also covering the eyes in black, whilst also wearing a completely different set of armor.

In the Heroes series, after being freed of the mask's brainwashing, he ends up becoming an affiliate of the Time Patrol, as [b]Bardock: Xeno[/b].

title: sei_shounagon
body:
Sei Shōnagon (lit. "lesser councilor of state Sei", real name unknown), (c. 966–1017 or later)

A Japanese court lady (女房 [i]nyoubo[/i]) and diarist who served the [[fujiwara_no_teishi|Empress Teishi]] (Sadako) around the year 1000 during the middle [[Heian]] period. She was involved in a court rivalry with [[murasaki_shikibu_(kimi_no_tame_nara_shineru)|Murasaki Shikibu]], lady-in-waiting to second empress consort [[fujiwara_no_shoushi|Shoushi]]. Her fate is uncertain, by most accounts either taking up Buddhist vows or marrying a provincial governor. 

She was an influential figure in Japanese literature, being best known as the author of [i]The Pillow Book[/i] (枕草子 [i]makura no sōshi[/i]). The book is both a personal diary and an eclectic collection of lists, musings and poetry, a format that created the genre of [i]zuihitsu[/i] (随筆) that is often compared to the contemporary medium of blogging. 

h4.See also

* "Wikipedia article":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sei_Shōnagon
